#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:3
msgid "nginx: Basic Load Balancing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:6
msgid "1) Create Upstream Servers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:12
msgid ""
"Create a server with a description and IP of the server. The priority is "
"not important if you have a single server. It is used as a weight for "
"round robin. Servers with a higher weight will receive more traffic."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:16
msgid "2) Create An Upstream"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:20
msgid ""
"Group upstream servers to an upstream. An upstream is a group of servers "
"to load balance between. Give it a useful name and choose the previously "
"created server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:25
msgid ""
"Upstream verification is enabled by default (**TLS: Verify Certificate** "
"checkbox). Server names in the upstream certificate are compared with the"
" name in the **TLS: Servername override** field. For successful "
"verification, it is necessary that OPNsense trusts the certificate of the"
" certification authority that issued the upstreams certificate. You can "
"further restrict the list of trusted CA's in the **TLS: Trusted "
"Certificate** field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:28
msgid "3) Create A Location"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:32
msgid ""
"Locations are are used to map URLs to upstreams, directories, settings "
"and so on. In our case we want to proxy the request to the previously "
"created upstream. If we want to match everything, we use \"/\" without a "
"special matcher. Now save the location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:38
msgid "4) Create A HTTP Server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:42
msgid ""
"In the last step, we have to create a port. This happens in a \"http\" "
"block, which contains some basic configuration and the location blocks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:45
msgid ""
"Enter the domain name into the \"Server Name\" field and select the "
"previously created location. If you want to use support TLS, you have to "
"add a certificate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:49
msgid "5) Restart nginx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/nginx.rst:53
msgid ""
"Click the reload button and you are done. You may need to open some ports"
" in the firewall if you have not done that yet. Since you are directly on"
" the firewall, There is no need to use NAT similar workaround."
msgstr ""

